Instruction: With the good battery still installed and 12 V confirmed at the battery, use a continuity tester/ohmmeter (with the battery temporarily removed for resistance checks) to trace the positive path from the battery’s + contact through the PCB/wiring to the PSU output (+) terminal. Verify: (1) continuity from battery + to the point where the PSU LED/resistor branch connects; (2) continuity from that node to the PSU output (+) terminal; and (3) whether the PSU LED/resistor branch is incorrectly tied between the two output terminals instead of across + and −. Look for an open trace, short between the two output terminals, or miswired connection causing the + and − outputs to be shorted together at 12 V.
