- load_cable_neg: Load Input Cable (−)

Instruction: Disconnect the PSU output cables from the rest of the system so the PSU is completely isolated. With the battery installed and 12 V confirmed at the PSU cables, use an ohmmeter to measure resistance between the two free PSU output connectors going toward the control modules/load. Determine whether there is a low‑ohm short between the external + and − lines, and if so progressively disconnect segments (control module 1, then 2, etc.) to localize which module or cable pair is creating the ~1 Ω short.
